<problem display_name="Orthogonal or not? 2" linenum="352" tex_filename="./block4/innerproducts.tex" showanswer="finished" attempts="1" rerandomize="per_student">
  <text>
    <p>
Let [mathjaxinline]f(x) = 1[/mathjaxinline] and let [mathjaxinline]g(x) = \sin x[/mathjaxinline]. </p>
    <p>
In the vector space [mathjaxinline]C[0,\pi ][/mathjaxinline] with inner product [mathjaxinline]\langle f,g\rangle = \int _0^{\pi } f(x)g(x) \  dx[/mathjaxinline], are [mathjaxinline]f[/mathjaxinline] and [mathjaxinline]g[/mathjaxinline] orthogonal? </p>
    <p>
      <optionresponse>
        <optioninput options="('Yes','No')" correct="No"/>
      </optionresponse>
    </p>
    <p>
In the vector space [mathjaxinline]C[-\pi ,\pi ][/mathjaxinline] with inner product [mathjaxinline]\langle f,g\rangle = \int _{-\pi }^{\pi } f(x)g(x) \  dx[/mathjaxinline], are [mathjaxinline]f[/mathjaxinline] and [mathjaxinline]g[/mathjaxinline] orthogonal? </p>
    <p>
      <optionresponse>
        <optioninput options="('Yes','No')" correct="Yes"/>
      </optionresponse>
    </p>
    <p>
      <solution>
        <font color="blue">Answer: </font>
        <font color="blue">
          <p>
 In the first space [mathjaxinline]C[0,\pi ][/mathjaxinline], we calculate </p>
          <table id="a0000000191" class="equation" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="7" style="table-layout:auto">
            <tr>
              <td class="equation" style="width:80%;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;border-style:hidden">[mathjax]\langle f, g\rangle = \int _0^\pi \sin x \  dx = 2,[/mathjax]</td>
              <td class="eqnnum" style="width:20%;vertical-align:middle;text-align:left;border-style:hidden"/>
            </tr>
          </table>
          <p>
 so [mathjaxinline]f[/mathjaxinline] and [mathjaxinline]g[/mathjaxinline] are not orthogonal. However, in the second space, we have </p>
          <table id="a0000000192" class="equation" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="7" style="table-layout:auto">
            <tr>
              <td class="equation" style="width:80%;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;border-style:hidden">[mathjax]\langle f, h\rangle = \int _{-\pi }^\pi \sin x \  dx = 0,[/mathjax]</td>
              <td class="eqnnum" style="width:20%;vertical-align:middle;text-align:left;border-style:hidden"/>
            </tr>
          </table>
          <p>
 so [mathjaxinline]f[/mathjaxinline] and [mathjaxinline]g[/mathjaxinline] <em>are</em> orthogonal in [mathjaxinline]C[-\pi ,\pi ][/mathjaxinline].  </p>
        </font>
      </solution>
    </p>
  </text>
</problem>
